@kylelangham I really appreciate that you are taking this up! It has been a long battle with Dfinity, for them to understand that you need to focus not just solely on the tech. But on communities, the people that will actually help grow the ecosystem.

I also appreciate that you offered to fund a community 12 month initiative, but this doesn‚Äôt seem to have had any effect and it‚Äôs too long a time frame. Would you guys fund some smaller initiatives, even small rewards for a meme contest or anything that the community can have fun and engage with?

You also need to step back sometimes. What if PokedStudio had launched Bots on Ethereum, that level of art would have been huge. Jon is the creator of these flagship projects, but I feel that Dfinity is letting him down as well.

I would imagine at the very top of the list was helping to foster permissionless NFT standards. I doubt they would have given so much support to a standard that required the NFTs to be transferred first for integration into all but one marketplace, *especially with their own market-leading collections*.

@kylelangham What am I supposed to think when the Dev that was in the process of making FlowerDAOs collections open mentions to me that he's not sure that the other collections will ever be switched over to the decentralized standard and come to find out he had been hired by the foundation who again also happens to control the highest grossing NFT collection on ICP that is also hardcoded for commissions to go directly to Toniq. 

From my perspective, why couldn't it have just been finished on-the-side?

